react-a11y-disclosure is a small React hook for building disclosure widgets: the “button toggles a panel” pattern behind accordions, show/hide sections, and mobile nav drawers. It wires up the right ARIA attributes and keeps button and region IDs in sync so assistive technologies announce state correctly.

## Design goals

- Minimal surface: one hook, no imposed markup beyond what the pattern needs.
- Composable: you keep control of styling and DOM structure; the hook focuses on behavior and accessibility contracts.
